HEADWORD: chainsaw
<hw>chain"saw`</hw> <pr>(ch⟦amac⟧n"s⟦add⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>a
portable power saw having teeth that are linked to form an endless
chain, rotated about two pivot points by a power mechanism, such as an
electric motor or a gasoline engine.</def> <note>They are used to
efficiently cut trees, logs, or thick branches out of doors.</note>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> chain saw.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

